cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with pedestrian detection in crowded scenes, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel bounding box regression loss, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The proposed method also involves object localization, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper deals with video analysis, which is a subfield of cs.MM (Multimedia).
